  "body": "*Title*: *Fault Delay: support float type percent*\r\n\r\n*Description*:\r\nThe `percent` field in the config of Fault Delay is limited to [uint32](https://www.envoyproxy.io/docs/envoy/v1.7.0/api-v2/config/filter/fault/v2/fault.proto.html?highlight=fault%20delay).\r\nhttps://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/1fdb6386c4bb42748530d7a9bf58ded644d77749/api/envoy/config/filter/fault/v2/fault.proto#L27\r\nHowever, for upstream clusters with heavy traffic, even 1% can be an exceedingly large number of requests. Would be useful to be able to specify percent as a float, e.g., 0.001% ",
